<h3 id="course-description">Course Description</h3>
<p><strong>Welcome to the course “Power Automate Fundamentals”</strong></p>
<p>Power Automate is a tool by Microsoft that automates repetitive tasks across different apps and services. It’s user-friendly, letting you create workflows easily by connecting triggers (like receiving an email) to actions (like sending a message). It works with various Microsoft apps and third-party services, making it versatile for different needs.</p>
<p>Whether you’re new to Power Automate or looking to enhance your proficiency, you’re in the perfect spot! In this comprehensive course, participants will dive into the world of automation using Power Automate to streamline their workflows and enhance productivity.</p>
<p>The course begins with an introduction to the fundamentals of Power Automate, including its features, capabilities, and benefits. We will learn how to create automated workflows, trigger actions based on specific events, and manage flow runs effectively.</p>
<p>As the course progresses, we will explore advanced topics such as:</p>
<ul>
<li>Triggers and Trigger’s Conditions</li>
<li>Expressions in Power Automate</li>
<li>Implementing approval workflows and tracking progress using Power Automate</li>
<li>Utilizing advanced data manipulation techniques with Power Automate to process and transform data.</li>
</ul>
<p>By the end of the course, participants will have the skills and knowledge to design, deploy, and manage complex automation solutions using Power Automate, empowering them to streamline their workflows and drive business efficiency. Enrol now and discover the transformative potential of automation to revolutionize your workflow.</p>
<h3 id="what-is-in-this-course">What is in this course?</h3>
<ul>
<li>Overview of Power Platform</li>
<li>Understanding Flow Trigger</li>
<li>Creating Flow with Conditional Logic</li>
<li>Designing Approval Flows</li>
<li>Data Transformations</li>
<li>Power Automate Flow Expressions</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="who-this-course-is-for">Who this course is for:</h3>
<ul>
<li>Professionals seeking to streamline their daily tasks and boost productivity</li>
<li>Individuals interested in automating repetitive processes across various applications and services</li>
<li>IT professionals aiming to optimize processes within their organizations</li>
<li>Those looking to integrate Power Automate with Microsoft apps and third-party services to meet diverse needs.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="are-there-any-course-requirements-or-prerequisites">Are there any course requirements or prerequisites?</h3>
<ul>
<li>There are no prerequisites for this course.</li>
</ul>

